  "texts": [
    "We find that neither Chemprop nor ChemBERTa perform consistently better across all 10 ADEs.",
    "Scaffold-stratifying reduced performance, resulting in a best model test-set AUROC of 0.548-0.719 per ADR.",
    "In particular, ADEs 4 and 6 in particular drop significantly when scaffold stratification is applied, suggesting that their initial performance with random-split was confounded by train/test information leakage.",
    "Additionally, we hypothesize this dataset may not be large enough to achieve optimal performance in training deep learning models for this task.",
    "The incorporation of additional data, such as simulated data, may improve performance."
  ],
